Put a #pot of water on high heat and bring to the boil. Cut the @British turkey steaks{2} into 1cm wide strips. Sprinkle over the @Chinese five spice{1/4} and mix well. Leave to marinate. Wash your hands, knife and #chopping board and then get on with the rest of your prep.

Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and thinly slice. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice thinly into half moon shapes.

Chop off the @spring onion{1} roots and slice them as thinly as you can. Peel and grate the @ginger{1/2} and @garlic clove{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{5} leaves.

Pop the @egg noodle nests{2} into the boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #colander and then run under cold water until the noodles are cold.

> Tip: This is to stop them cooking anymore.

While the noodles are cooking, heat a large #frying pan or #wok on high heat and add 1 tbsp of @oil{}. Cook the turkey strips for ~{4%minutes} making sure they get nicely browned.

> Tip: Cook the turkey in batches to make sure the meat does not stew.

Transfer the turkey to a #bowl and keep until later.

Wipe the pan with a piece of #kitchen paper and then add another 1 tbsp of @oil{}. When the oil is very hot, add the peppers and cook for ~{3%minutes} before adding the red onion. Cook for another ~{2%minutes} and then pop the turkey back into the pan. Add the ginger and garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute} before stirring in the drained noodles, @soy sauce{3} and @rice vinegar{1}.

Toss well, to make sure all the ingredients are combined and cook for another ~{1%minute} to make sure your noodles are piping hot.

Finish your stir-fry by adding the chopped spring onion and as much coriander as you like. Serve immediately and enjoy!